---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import siteConfig from '../../site.config';
const lastUpdated = 'April 19, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service — SupplementScout" description="The terms that govern your use of supplementsscout.net, including medical disclaimers, content usage, and liability.">
  <article class="policy">
    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <span class="sep">/</span>
      <span class="current">Terms of Service</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="page-header">
      <span class="page-label">Legal</span>
      <h1>Terms of Service.<br/><em>The rules of the road.</em></h1>
      <div class="header-rule"></div>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="content">
      <section>
        <h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>By accessing or using <a href="https://supplementsscout.net">supplementsscout.net</a> (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service (the &ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) and our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. If you do not agree, please do not use the Site.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Not Medical Advice</h2>
        <p class="callout"><strong>Content on this Site is editorial and educational only. It is not medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment, and is not a substitute for consultation with a qualified healthcare professional.</strong></p>
        <p>{siteConfig.siteName} publishes reviews, comparisons, and guides about dietary supplements, vitamins, and nutrition products. We do our best to reference peer-reviewed research, but individual physiology, medication regimens, and health conditions vary enormously. What is safe and effective for one person may be harmful for another.</p>
        <p>You should always consult a qualified healthcare professional (physician, registered dietitian, pharmacist, or equivalent) before starting, stopping, or changing any supplement, especially if you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Are pregnant, nursing, or trying to conceive.</li>
          <li>Are under 18 years of age.</li>
          <li>Take any prescription or over-the-counter medication (many supplements interact with blood thinners, antidepressants, blood pressure medication, thyroid medication, and others).</li>
          <li>Have a diagnosed medical condition (including but not limited to liver, kidney, cardiovascular, endocrine, autoimmune, or psychiatric conditions).</li>
          <li>Are scheduled for surgery within two weeks.</li>
          <li>Have a history of allergies or adverse reactions to supplements, herbs, or food ingredients.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Never delay or disregard professional medical advice because of something you have read on this Site. If you think you may have a medical emergency, call your doctor or emergency services immediately.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>FDA Disclaimer</h2>
        <p class="callout"><strong>These statements have not been evaluated by the Food and Drug Administration. Products discussed on this Site are not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease.</strong></p>
        <p>Dietary supplements are regulated by the FDA as food, not as drugs. The FDA does not approve supplements for safety or efficacy before they reach the market. References to studies, ingredients, or traditional uses on this Site are for educational purposes and do not constitute claims of medical benefit.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Product Formulations Change</h2>
        <p>Supplement brands reformulate frequently. Ingredients, doses, excipients, allergen profiles, third-party testing certifications, country of manufacture, and label claims can change between batches without notice. Our reviews reflect the product as it existed at the time of testing.</p>
        <p><strong>Before buying or consuming any supplement mentioned on this Site, verify the current Supplement Facts panel, ingredient list, and allergen warnings on the manufacturer&rsquo;s official website or on the physical label.</strong> If anything on the current label differs from what we describe, trust the label, not our review, and contact the manufacturer with any questions.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Drug Interactions and Allergies</h2>
        <p>Many dietary supplements interact with prescription and over-the-counter medications. Examples include (but are not limited to) St. John&rsquo;s Wort reducing the effectiveness of oral contraceptives and antidepressants; fish oil, garlic, ginkgo, and vitamin E increasing bleeding risk when combined with anticoagulants; calcium and iron impairing absorption of thyroid medication and certain antibiotics; and grapefruit-related compounds affecting statin metabolism.</p>
        <p>This is not an exhaustive list. You are responsible for checking for interactions with your pharmacist or physician before combining a supplement with any medication. If you experience an adverse reaction, stop the product immediately and seek medical attention.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Editorial Content</h2>
        <p>{siteConfig.siteName} publishes reviews, comparisons, and guides about supplements and nutrition products. Our goal is to help readers make informed decisions. Content is provided on an &ldquo;as is&rdquo; and &ldquo;as available&rdquo; basis and is for general informational purposes only. We do not make guarantees about the accuracy, completeness, or fitness for a particular purpose of any information on the Site.</p>
        <p>Product prices, features, and availability change often. Always verify pricing and terms on the vendor&rsquo;s website before purchasing.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Affiliate Links and Commercial Relationships</h2>
        <p>We earn affiliate commissions when readers click some links on the Site and purchase products from third parties. This is explained in full on our <a href="/disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a> page. Commercial relationships do not influence our editorial rankings; see our <a href="/how-we-test">How We Test</a> methodology for details.</p>
        <p><strong>As an Amazon Associate, SupplementScout earns from qualifying purchases.</strong></p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>All original content on the Site &mdash; including articles, images, logos, design, code, and branding &mdash; is owned by {siteConfig.siteName} or its contributors and is protected by copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws.</p>
        <p>You may:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>View and share links to Site content for personal, non-commercial use.</li>
          <li>Quote short excerpts for journalism, commentary, or criticism with clear attribution and a link back to the original article.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You may not, without our prior written permission:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Republish or redistribute substantial portions of Site content.</li>
          <li>Use Site content to train machine learning models, scrape for commercial databases, or generate derivative commercial products.</li>
          <li>Use our name, logo, or design in a way that suggests endorsement or affiliation.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the Site to violate any applicable law or regulation.</li>
          <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Site, its servers, or networks connected to it.</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any portion of the Site or related systems.</li>
          <li>Submit false, misleading, or spammy content via forms, comments, or other inputs.</li>
          <li>Use automated systems (bots, scrapers, harvesters) to access the Site in ways that exceed reasonable personal use or violate our robots.txt.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Third-Party Sites and Products</h2>
        <p>The Site links to products and websites operated by third parties. We do not control and are not responsible for the content, privacy practices, security, product quality, or terms of those third parties. Accessing or purchasing from third parties is at your own risk.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>User-Submitted Content</h2>
        <p>If you submit content through our forms, email, or any other channel (for example, feedback on an article), you grant {siteConfig.siteName} a non-exclusive, royalty-free, worldwide license to use, publish, and adapt that content in connection with the Site, with attribution where reasonable. You are responsible for ensuring that any content you submit does not infringe anyone else&rsquo;s rights.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>THE SITE AND ITS CONTENT ARE PROVIDED &ldquo;AS IS&rdquo; AND &ldquo;AS AVAILABLE&rdquo; WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, NON-INFRINGEMENT, OR ACCURACY. WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT THE SITE WILL BE UNINTERRUPTED, SECURE, OR ERROR-FREE, OR THAT ANY INFORMATION PROVIDED IS CURRENT, COMPLETE, OR APPLICABLE TO YOUR PERSONAL HEALTH SITUATION.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, {siteConfig.siteName.toUpperCase()} AND ITS CONTRIBUTORS WILL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS OR REVENUES, OR ANY LOSS OF DATA, USE, GOODWILL, HEALTH, OR OTHER TANGIBLE OR INTANGIBLE LOSSES, ARISING FROM YOUR USE OF THE SITE, ANY CONTENT OBTAINED FROM IT, OR ANY PRODUCT PURCHASED AS A RESULT OF INFORMATION FOUND ON THE SITE. YOU ASSUME FULL RESPONSIBILITY FOR ANY DECISIONS YOU MAKE ABOUT YOUR HEALTH, DIET, OR SUPPLEMENT REGIMEN.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Indemnification</h2>
        <p>You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless {siteConfig.siteName} and its contributors from any claim, liability, damage, loss, or expense (including reasonable attorneys&rsquo; fees) arising out of your use of the Site or your violation of these Terms.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes to the Site and Terms</h2>
        <p>We may modify or discontinue any part of the Site at any time. We may also update these Terms from time to time; the &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date at the top of this page will reflect the most recent version. Your continued use of the Site after changes become effective constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction in which the Site operator is based, without regard to conflict-of-law principles. Any dispute arising out of or relating to the Site or these Terms will be resolved in the courts of that jurisdiction, unless otherwise required by applicable consumer protection law.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="contact">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about these Terms? Email <a href="mailto:hello@supplementsscout.net">hello@supplementsscout.net</a>.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .policy {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--ink-400);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .breadcrumb a { color: var(--ink-500); text-decoration: none; }
  .breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--ink-950); }
  .sep { color: var(--ink-300); }
  .current { color: var(--ink-400); }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    animation: fadeInUp var(--duration-slow) var(--ease-out) both;
  }

  .page-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ink-400);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-header h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-500);
  }

  .header-rule {
    height: 2px;
    width: 48px;
    background: var(--surface-inverse);
  }

  .updated {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--ink-400);
  }

  .content section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .content h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink-100);
  }

  .content section:first-child h2 {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .content p {
    color: var(--ink-700);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .content ul {
    color: var(--ink-700);
  }

  .content li {
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .content a {
    color: var(--ink-700);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .content a:hover { color: var(--ink-950); }

  .callout {
    padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-lg);
    border-left: 3px solid #10B981;
    background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.06);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .contact a {
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
</style>
